The paper uses game theoretic models to analyze parking behavior in urban centers, which falls under the category of computational social science (cs.SI). Specifically, the paper focuses on queuing games, which is a subfield of game theory (cs.GT) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the concept of social welfare, which is a topic in computational economics (cs.CE). Finally, the paper uses simulation to explore the occupancy-congestion relationship, which involves machine learning and data analysis (cs.LG).
